      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision on construct mechanical adequacy.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the regulatory QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly inform the design acceptance decision. These quantities are mechanistically linked to the failure modes (fatigue, permanent deformation) relevant to the COU. Relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
